    {
      "instruction": "<p>Score your<strong> sea bass</strong> <strong>fillet[s]</strong> by drawing a sharp knife through the skin 3 times on the diagonal, taking care not to cut all the way through, then season both sides with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat, then once hot, add the <strong>scored sea bass fillet[s]</strong>, skin side down, and cook for 5 min, then turn and cook for 1 min further until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
